    Hello there! I'm glad you managed to find this gem of an archive. This bit of text is just a brief intro to me and this archive.
    What you've got here is a selection of programs (at the time of writing, all CLI), which'll be useful to anyone who has even a remotely technical@{π link π} use for the Amiga@{≤ link ≤}, and could be very useful for any budding programmer (you'll have to excuse the messy code). If you've got this far through the text without quitting, then it proves (I hope) that you're willing to give my programs a try. @{b}*Don't be put of by these programs for at least a week.*@{ub} if you use these programs for a week, then I'm sure you'll consider some of them essential. I myself can't do without a number of them.
    The programs were all born out of my @{u}need@{uu} for a certain utility that I hadn't got, and I haven't wrote them just for the fun of it. I'm sure you'll find them useful, for example the DisplayBeep command can be used in ToolsDaemon, the Eko command (amazing program --- keep this on 'yer @{harddrive link "Wot no 'ardrive?"}) is useful for anyone who uses the shell, and it could have a useful place on a self-booting disk.
    If you've used my programs for a week and you still don't like them then you may get rid of them, but I my self have completely disregarded programs only to go back to them many months later to find they're the best thing since sliced bread.
    My inspiration for these programs came from Beavis & Butthead, Albert Einstein (1879 - 1955 R.I.P.), Steven Hawking, The cast of Friends, Martin Cloones, Curry, Quentin Tarantino, Richard Richard and Edward Elizabeth Hitler, Iron Maiden, Metallica, Mega Death (et al), the Amiga@{≤ link ≤}, Beer ...... (I think you get the picture)


