    One thing a lot of Amiga owners can't admit is that the Amiga has been dead for quite some time, but the emergence of new technology (maybe the PowerPC, but only maybe) could herald a new era for the Amiga. An OS 4, tower (et al), super processors, graphics boards etc. could revolutionise the way most people see a PC as only being an IBM compatible computer running the very latest version of Windows (95's been a massive improvement but it's still not a touch on the good old Amiga OS). One of the main ways to reestablish their market would have to be to introduce games the like of which most Amigans can only dream of, and a good suite of office proggys (to win against Office '97).
    I hope that one day soon, the Amiga will wipe out the virtual monopoly (be careful what you say Goody) that Microsoft has on the world.

